Description: Computes age-specific probabilities of outliving a target age (conditional survival P(T>tau|T>t)) and the probability that a randomly sampled individual of unknown age will outlive tau (O_tau). Does not assume proportional hazards or a parametric survival form. Supports pairwise comparison of O_tau across groups via Beta-KS bootstrap. See the TAUS manuscript for methodology.
